Here are both approaches using `IQueryAttributable` on the ViewModel.

**1. Register the route** in `AppShell.xaml.cs`:

```csharp
Routing.RegisterRoute("productdetails", typeof(ProductDetailsPage));
```

**2. Navigate from ProductListPage** (e.g., on CollectionView `SelectionChanged`):

```csharp
// Approach A — string query parameter
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"productdetails?productId={selectedProduct.Id}");

// Approach B — pass the full object
var parameters = new ShellNavigationQueryParameters
{
    { "product", selectedProduct }
};
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("productdetails", parameters);
```

**3. Receive on the ViewModel** with `IQueryAttributable`:

```csharp
public class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    private string _productId;
    private Product _product;

    public string ProductId
    {
        get => _productId;
        set => SetProperty(ref _productId, value);
    }

    public Product Product
    {
        get => _product;
        set => SetProperty(ref _product, value);
    }

    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Approach A — string parameter (arrives as string)
        if (query.TryGetValue("productId", out var id))
        {
            ProductId = id.ToString();
            // Load the full product from a service using the ID
        }

        // Approach B — full object (arrives as the original type)
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var obj) && obj is Product product)
        {
            Product = product;
            ProductId = product.Id;
        }
    }
}
```

**Key differences:**

| | Query string | `ShellNavigationQueryParameters` |
|---|---|---|
| **Data type** | String only | Any object |
| **Visible in URI** | Yes (`?productId=42`) | No |
| **Serialization** | You handle it | None needed |
| **Use when** | Simple IDs, primitives | Complex objects already in memory |

> **Tip:** Always `await` `GoToAsync` — fire-and-forget causes race conditions. And make sure `ProductDetailsPage` sets `BindingContext` to `ProductDetailsViewModel` (via DI or code-behind) so `ApplyQueryAttributes` is called on the VM.
